0.}"></span>
</p><p>In fact, the rounding error quickly becomes very small as <span clas=
s=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span> grows, being less =
than 0.1 for <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i> =E2=89=A5 4</span>, and less =
than 0.01 for <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i> =E2=89=A5 8</span>. This for=
mula is easily inverted to find an index of a Fibonacci number <span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">F</span>:
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
