          <mi>=CF=86<!-- =CF=86 --></mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <msup>
          <mi>=CF=88<!-- =CF=88 --></mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\sqrt {5}}F_=
{n}=3D\varphi ^{n}-\psi ^{n}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/b436885595c4c0ffcf815a0ddad385b86bdcef85" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -0.838ex; width:17.867ex; height:3.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {=
\sqrt {5}}F_{n}=3D\varphi ^{n}-\psi ^{n}.}"></span>
This can be used to prove Fibonacci identities.
</p><p>For example, to prove that <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-=
