<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Reciprocal_sums">Reciprocal=
 sums</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brac=
ket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DFibona=
cci_sequence&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D23" title=3D"Edit section: Rec=
iprocal sums"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]=
</span></span></div>
<p>Infinite sums over <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multiplicati=
ve_inverse" title=3D"Multiplicative inverse">reciprocal</a> Fibonacci numbe=
rs can sometimes be evaluated in terms of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Theta_function" title=3D"Theta function">theta functions</a>. For e=
xample, the sum of every odd-indexed reciprocal Fibonacci number can be wri=
tten as
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle \sum _{k=3D1}^{\infty }{\frac {1}{F_{2k-1}}}=3D{\frac {\sqrt {5=
}}{4}}\;\vartheta _{2}\!\left(0,{\frac {3-{\sqrt {5}}}{2}}\right)^{2},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <munderover>
          <mo>=E2=88=91<!-- =E2=88=91 --></mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>k</mi>
            <mo>=3D</mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">=E2=88=9E<!-- =E2=88=9E --></mi>
          </mrow>
        </munderover>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>1</mn>
            <msub>
              <mi>F</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>2</mn>
                <mi>k</mi>
                <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                <mn>1</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msub>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <msqrt>
              <mn>5</mn>
            </msqrt>
            <mn>4</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mspace width=3D"thickmathspace"></mspace>
        <msub>
          <mi>=CF=91<!-- =CF=91 --></mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>2</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mspace width=3D"negativethinmathspace"></mspace>
        <msup>
          <mrow>
            <mo>(</mo>
            <mrow>
              <mn>0</mn>
              <mo>,</mo>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mfrac>
                  <mrow>
                    <mn>3</mn>
                    <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
                    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                      <msqrt>
                        <mn>5</mn>
                      </msqrt>
                    </mrow>
                  </mrow>
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mfrac>
              </mrow>
            </mrow>
            <mo>)</mo>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>2</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
