 tree">Balance factors</a> green; heights red.<br>The keys in the left spin=
e are Fibonacci numbers.</figcaption></figure>
<ul><li>The Fibonacci numbers are important in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Analysis_of_algorithms" title=3D"Analysis of algorithms">compu=
tational run-time analysis</a> of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Euclidean_algorithm" title=3D"Euclidean algorithm">Euclid's algorithm</a> t=
o determine the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greatest_common_di=
visor" title=3D"Greatest common divisor">greatest common divisor</a> of two=
 integers: the worst case input for this algorithm is a pair of consecutive=
 Fibonacci numbers.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-73" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fibonacci_sequence#cite_note-73"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>71<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=
</li>
<li>Fibonacci numbers are used in a polyphase version of the <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Merge_sort" title=3D"Merge sort">merge sort</a> =
algorithm in which an unsorted list is divided into two lists whose lengths=
 correspond to sequential Fibonacci numbers=E2=80=94by dividing the list so=
 that the two parts have lengths in the approximate proportion <span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CF=86</span>. A tape-drive =
implementation of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polyphase_me=
rge_sort" title=3D"Polyphase merge sort">polyphase merge sort</a> was descr=
ibed in <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Art_of_Computer_Pro=
gramming" title=3D"The Art of Computer Programming">The Art of Computer Pro=
gramming</a></i>.</li>
<li><span class=3D"anchor" id=3D"Fibonacci_Tree"></span>A Fibonacci tree is=
 a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binary_tree" title=3D"Binary tr=
ee">binary tree</a> whose child trees (recursively) differ in <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tree_height" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Tre=
e height">height</a> by exactly 1. So it is an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/AVL_tree" title=3D"AVL tree">AVL tree</a>, and one with the fe=
west nodes for a given height=E2=80=94the "thinnest" AVL tree. These trees =
have a number of vertices that is a Fibonacci number minus one, an importan=
t fact in the analysis of AVL trees.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-74" class=3D"refere=
nce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fibonacci_sequence#cite_note-=
74"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>72<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup></li>
<li>Fibonacci numbers are used by some <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Pseudorandom_number_generator" title=3D"Pseudorandom number generator"=
>pseudorandom number generators</a>.</li>
<li>Fibonacci numbers arise in the analysis of the <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Fibonacci_heap" title=3D"Fibonacci heap">Fibonacci heap</a=
> data structure.</li>
<li>A one-dimensional optimization method, called the <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fibonacci_search_technique" title=3D"Fibonacci search t=
echnique">Fibonacci search technique</a>, uses Fibonacci numbers.<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-75" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Fibonacci_sequence#cite_note-75"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>73<sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>The Fibonacci number series is used for optional <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Lossy_compression" title=3D"Lossy compression">lossy com=
pression</a> in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interchange_Fi=
le_Format" title=3D"Interchange File Format">IFF</a> <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/8SVX" title=3D"8SVX">8SVX</a> audio file format used on =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amiga" title=3D"Amiga">Amiga</a> c=
omputers. The number series <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Compan=
ding" title=3D"Companding">compands</a> the original audio wave similar to =
logarithmic methods such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%CE%9C=
-law" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"=CE=9C-law">=CE=BC-law</a>.<sup id=3D"=
cite_ref-76" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/F=
ibonacci_sequence#cite_note-76"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>74<spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-77" class=3D=
"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fibonacci_sequence#cit=
e_note-77"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>75<span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>Some Agile teams use a modified series called the "Modified Fibonacci S=
eries" in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Planning_poker" title=3D=
"Planning poker">planning poker</a>, as an estimation tool. Planning Poker =
is a formal part of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scaled_agi=
le_framework" title=3D"Scaled agile framework">Scaled Agile Framework</a>.<=
sup id=3D"cite_ref-78" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Fibonacci_sequence#cite_note-78"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</s=
pan>76<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fibonacci_coding" title=3D"Fib=
onacci coding">Fibonacci coding</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Negafibonacci_coding" title=3D=
"Negafibonacci coding">Negafibonacci coding</a></li></ul>
