on also follows the Fibonacci sequence.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-xcs_94-1" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fibonacci_sequence#=
cite_note-xcs-94"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>92<span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">]</span></a></sup> A male individual has an X chromosome, which =
he received from his mother, and a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Y_chromosome" title=3D"Y chromosome">Y chromosome</a>, which he received f=
rom his father. The male counts as the "origin" of his own X chromosome (<s=
pan class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-m=
ath-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmln=
